# Vega Chart - KX Dashboards

Original URL: https://code.kx.com/dashboards/vegachart/

# Vega Chart

![Screenshot](../img/vega/vegasamples.jpg)

Component that renders a chart using [Vega](https://vega.github.io/vega/)
Chart library. Demonstration of capabilities of the library can be found in
[Vega Example Gallery](https://vega.github.io/vega/examples/).

## Set up

  1. Set the data source.

  2. Specify the JSON for the _Vega Config_.

## Basics

![Screenshot](../img/vega/vegaconfigbasics.png)

_Name_

    A name for the component provided by the user. 

### _Data Source_

A [query](../datasources/) or [analytic](../datasources/). When set, values of
first _data_ item in _Vega Config_ will be overwritten.

### _Vega Config_

![Screenshot](../img/vega/vegaconfigjson.jpg)

Specification in JSON format of multiple aspects of the chart:

  * data handling and transformations
  * visual representation
  * behavior

Documentation about available options can be found on [Vega
Website](https://vega.github.io/vega/docs/).

Auto stretch

Chart will automatically fit available space if neither _width_ nor _height_
is specified.

#### Data Source override

External resource in Vega configuration can referenced as shown in code below.

    
    
    {
        "data": [{
            "name": "vectors",
            "url": "data/windvectors.csv",
            "format": {"type": "csv", "parse": "auto"}      
        }],
        .. 
    

Setting _Data Source_ will modify the configuration above with actual values:

    
    
    {
        "data": [{
            "name": "vectors",
            "values": [
                {
                    longitude:7.5,
                    latitude:4.3,
                    ..
                    speed:3.12
                },
                ..
            ]
        }],
        ..         
    

Notice that the _url_ and _format_ properties are replaced with _values_.

### _Render Type_

Controls whether the chart is rendered as `<canvas>`(faster) or `<svg>`.

